The issue with the code is that the `StringTokenizer` is not properly handling the case where the input string does not contain any commas. The `nextToken()` method will throw a `NoSuchElementException` if there are no more tokens to be retrieved from the input string. To fix this issue, you can add a check to see if the `nextToken()` method has thrown a `NoSuchElementException` before trying to retrieve the next token. Here's the updated code:
```java
Carmap = new HashMap<String,Car>();
//Change file path accordingly
File f = new File("C:\\XXX\\XXX\\XXX\\CarFaxDB.txt");
