if (f.exists()){
    String data[] = readFile(f);
    for (int i =0; i<data.length; i++){
        if (data[i] != null){
            String line = data[i];
            StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(line,",");
            while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
                String VIN = st.nextToken();
                String carMake = st.nextToken();
                String carModel = st.nextToken();
                int carYear = Integer.parseInt(st.nextToken());
                data[i]= line;
                Car car = new Car(VIN, carMake, carModel, carYear);
                Carmap.put(car.getVIN(), car);
            }
        }
    }
}
```
In this updated code, we use a `while` loop to iterate over the tokens in the input string. We check if there are more tokens using the `hasMoreTokens()` method before trying to retrieve the next token using `nextToken()`. This ensures that we don't try to retrieve a token that doesn't exist.
